programme.desc: Derek Brockway joins the 'surf dudes' when he visits St Bride's Bay, Pembrokeshire - but still needs a bit more practice. On his walk from Little Haven to Solva, he also learns about a UFO sighting that stunned the world, brushes up on his life-saving skills, helps a local artist create a giant mural and is blown away by the stunning scenery

programme.title: Robson Green's Weekend Escapes: Mark Benton
programme.desc: Actor Mark Benton joins Robson on a Scottish road trip in East Lothian. Robson introduces his friend to bird watching in Musselburgh and books them into a cookery school in Longniddry to prepare lobster - where Mark is dazzled by a baked potato. The duo stay over in a converted double decker bus, before attempting a scaled-down Highland Games, and welly-tossing antics ensue

programme.title: Flog It!: London 27
programme.desc: Will Axon and Thomas Plant value items at London Zoo in Regent's Park, including a Ducati camera, a painting by Walter Sickert's brother and a pair of Zulu spears. programme.title: Robson Green's Weekend Escapes: Gail Porter
programme.desc: Robson heads to the Cairngorms with presenter Gail Porter. The pair mountain bike through the countryside around Loch Malachie and take in the views. They sit patiently to get a glimpse of an osprey in the wild before checking into their glamping site digs. Poetry, fresh air and landscapes dotted with Highland cattle make for a restful weekend

programme.title: Winterwatch
programme.desc: Chris Packham, Michaela Strachan and Iolo Williams broadcast from the Mount Stewart estate on the shores of Strangford Lough. The team slow down and discover the quiet wonders of winter, from wading birds gathering along the lough to the hardy woodland residents thriving among ancient trees. Featuring expert insight, intimate encounters and those first magical moments of the season

programme.sub-title: Our Rarest Find and Biggest Dig

programme.title: The Piano
programme.desc: A mute Scottish widow travels to New Zealand with her daughter, and enters into a loveless arranged marriage. Her one means of self-expression is her piano, which her husband sells to a gruff settler who has adopted Maori culture. He allows her to play the instrument, and through their shared love of music, a passionate affair develops. Period drama, starring Oscar-winners Holly Hunter and Anna Paquin. With Harvey Keitel and Sam Neill

programme.title: What We Do in the Shadows: Headhunting
programme.desc: Guillermo gets a new job, and Colin helps Laszlo make a new friend. Comedy, starring Matt Berry, Mark Proksch and Harvey Guilln

programme.title: Can You Keep a Secret?
programme.desc: Debbie bans William from chocolate and Harry from sharing their secret with Neha. But someone else now knows about William - and wants a cut of the cash

programme.title: Amanda & Alan's Greek Job
programme.desc: Inspired by Gerald Durrell's love of wildlife, Amanda and Alan design their first ever children's bedroom and visit Gerald's widow Lee for inspiration. Amanda calls in help to build a bespoke L-shaped bunk bed while Alan pulls a shift at the donkey sanctuary before the pair swap out their boiler suits for swim suits and head to Corfu's famous water park Aqualand

programme.sub-title: Hidden Treasures and a Full-Throttle Find Season 5, Episode 12
programme.desc: After losing their mum to Alzheimer's disease, siblings Annette and Bruce face the task of clearing their family home - and the lifetime of memories within. But before the house can be put up for sale, the siblings need to fix repairs caused by a leak. Izzie Balmer and JJ Chalmers uncover treasures to raise the money required, from a neglected trike motorcycle to vintage watches

programme.title: Flog It!: Derby 6
programme.desc: Paul Martin is joined by experts Michael Baggott and Caroline Hawley on a visit to Haddon Hall in Derbyshire, where the team picks out a selection of interesting antiques and collectibles to be sold at a local auction. Michael finds an impressive scent bottle, and Caroline gets a glimpse into the past by looking through a stereoscopic viewer. Paul also looks around the property, and meets the current owner, Lord Edward Manners

programme.desc: Nadia Jae, Tamzin Outhwaite, Nigel Planer and Steen Raskopoulos test their general knowledge skills in a variety of trivia-based games

programme.title: Robson Green's Weekend Escapes: Rishi Nair
programme.desc: Robson invites fellow Grantchester actor Rishi Nair to visit Northumberland and explore the great outdoors. They head to Kielder forest to learn about foraging, overnight in a yurt in Northumberland National Park and explore the local bat population. A session making and painting Roman-style pots ends their weekend escape

programme.title: Winterwatch
programme.desc: Chris Packham, Michaela Strachan and Iolo Williams observe secretive badgers emerging after dusk and elusive pine martens, who have been reclaiming their place in Northern Ireland's woodlands. Also, the hidden lives unfolding beneath the winter canopy. Alongside the stories from Mount Stewart, there are stories from across the UK, capturing a rich variety of wildlife

programme.title: A House Through Time
programme.desc: It's 1940, and in London, the threat of invasion by Germany has become very real. Montagu Mansions resident Timothy Corsellis begins training as an RAF pilot, but begins to regret his decision when facing the prospect of bombing innocent civilians. His older sister, Mary, gets involved in supporting victims of the bombing in Stepney

programme.title: Digging for Britain: A Mysterious Bone Box and Admiral Nelson's Favourite Ship
programme.sub-title: A Mysterious Bone Box and Admiral Nelson's Favourite Ship
programme.desc: Featuring an ft slipway in the New Forest where Admiral Nelson's favourite ship was built, an Anglo-Saxon cemetery where a host of well-preserved and rare objects have been found, and finds from Trinity College, Oxford. Plus, a late Roman cemetery that features an intricate bone box and part of a Roman bone flute, and a tangle of delicate Iron Age objects that have to be carefully micro-excavated in Kent

programme.title: One Foot in the Grave: The Valley of Fear
programme.sub-title: The Valley of Fear Season 1, Episode 3
programme.desc: The Meldrew household is disrupted by a pesky plumber whose penchant for morbid practical jokes would try the patience of a saint. Victor decides it's time to call a neighbourhood watch system after he's mugged and graffiti is spray painted on the side of the Meldrews' house. David Renwick's award-winning comedy, starring Richard Wilson and Annette Crosbie

programme.title: The Road Dance
programme.desc: Kirsty Macleod dreams of a better life away from the isolation that suffocates her in a small village on an island in the Outer Hebrides. Suppressing these aspirations, she sees her lover Murdo conscripted for service in the First World War, soon to set off and fight alongside the other young men from the village. A dance is held in their honour the evening before they depart, and it's on this fateful night that Kirsty's life takes a dramatic and tragic turn. Period drama, starring Hermione Corfield

programme.sub-title: Cities Reinvented E02 - Tokyo - The Urban Village Concept
programme.desc: The Greater Tokyo Area is the worlds most populous metropolitan region, and it is continuing to grow at a fast pace. Urban-planning solutions are urgently needed to prevent Tokyo from choking on its own growth. Strategies include raising density, promoting shared housing and micro-homes, and investing in urban villages, neighborhoods where people can live, work and spend their leisure time.

programme.title: DW Cities Reinvented
programme.sub-title: Cities Reinvented E03 - Singapore - Embracing Nature
programme.desc: Singapore is arguably the worlds most modern metropolis. The small island state with a growing population needs to plan land use and construction carefully. It has become a pioneer in eco-friendly energy-saving urban development. The regulations are stringent: any green space lost when a new building goes up must be replaced somewhere else. The city is creating a new generation of green skyscrapers that harvest rainwater and run on solar power.

programme.title: Gordon Ramsays Great Escape
programme.sub-title: Gordon Ramsays Great Escape S01 E01 - India Part 1
programme.desc: Gordons odyssey begins in the north, home of our curry house classics. On board an express train hes thrown in at the deep end and experiences a back-to-basics baptism of fire, cooking for its many passengers in the trains cramped pantry car and getting travel sick while hes making curry. In stark contrast he then meets his match working for a cantankerous royal chef, preparing a biryani with a difference for a huge wedding feast before venturing into the jungle where he gets eaten alive by ants when he scales a 40-foot tree in search of the local tribes favourite delicacy. Then its on to Delhi to cook at the restaurant that invented tandoori chicken, where Gordon puts into practice everything hes learnt for a tough crowd of Delhi food critics.

programme.title: Scottish Islands with Ben Fogle
programme.sub-title: Scottish Islands With Ben Fogle S01 E01 - Inner Hebrides NB
programme.desc: Ben Fogle journeys across Scotlands sacred Inner Hebrides, exploring the spiritual heritage of its remote islands. From Tiree to Iona, he discovers deep-rooted faith, community resilience, and the enduring power of pilgrimage and place.

programme.title: Into the Rising Sun
programme.desc: In this episode, Scott Wilson trades the bustle of Japans cities for the tranquility of its countryside. His journey begins in a traditional onsen town, where he experiences the rituals of Japanese bathing and fine dining. Along the way, he wields a katana with a master, visits one of the last swordsmiths still forging blades by hand, and explores the roots of udon noodles and mustard-making. Riding deep into Shikoku, Scott encounters disappearing villages brought back to life by creativity and community spirit. The adventure ends under the stars by a mountain river, celebrating Japans enduring balance of tradition, resilience, and nature.

programme.title: Alan Cummings: Paradise Homes
programme.sub-title: Alan Cummings: Paradise Homes S01 E01 - Norfolk and Ontario
programme.desc: Alan takes to the water of the Norfolk Broads, where he meets a family who have created their paradise home in a beautifully serene setting by the water. There is more than meets the eye as he discovers the treacherous pike and quicksand close by, learning that practicality is also important in creating paradise! He then dives into the Canadian wilderness to visit an old cabin-converted magical woodland playground. But will he be able to avoid the grizzly bears on his own quest for paradise?

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team
programme.desc: Dreams are on the line as the tryouts for the Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders 2013-2014 squad begin.

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team
programme.desc: The pressure is mounting as 54 new candidates compete with 32 returning veterans for an invitation into the famed Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders training camp.

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team
programme.desc: Training camp begins at the Cowboys famous training facility, Valley Ranch. First Meeting is filled with excitement and energy until Kelli calls a special meeting of the veterans.

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team
programme.desc: The "scariest night of training camp" kicks off this dramatic episode as the girls learn the dreaded jumpsplit! It's mind over body, as the girls attempt this famed and required move.

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team
programme.desc: The ladies are really challenged when guest choreographer DJ Guthrie teaches them a new dance style. Kelli and Judy have some tough decisions to make about who will remain on the squad.

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team
